The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business
 Monday, May 03, 2004 				 Godfrey Phillips to revamp units
																								New Delhi, May 2 (PTI): Godfrey Phillips, a flagship of the K. K. Modi group, today announced that it will invest Rs 600 crore to modernise its existing cigarette-making facilities as part of its restructuring plan even though the government has banned smoking at public places and tobacco advertisement directly or indirectly. 																								This is in keeping with our objective to make the manufacturing capabilities in India on par with the international standards.. This will in turn facilitate and support our plans to increase our export business, said K. K. Modi, president of Godfrey Phillips India.																								The company will launch international brand of cigarette for the export market next month, he said.																								Announcing the investment plans, Modi said the entire money would be invested in plant modernisation in Mumbai and Ghaziabad to increase quality and productivity. 
